name: Wig & pen sequoia

name: Wig & pen velvet cream

name: Wig & pen Duncan
desc: Perhaps one of the mildest beers I've ever had but has a great balance between sour and salty. Deducting points because it's a mid strength

name: Asahi dry black
desc: A rather sweet taste compared to the regular asahi

name: Wet hopped oatmeal ale
desc: A lot more plain than I expected. There's a really slight oat aftertaste but I was hoping for it to dominate the beer

name: Single-take session ale
desc: Perhaps not the best beer at 10am. The Belgian flavour seemed a bit too wheaty

name: Tecate
desc: Pretty plain lager, easy drinking. +1 because of the giant can
brewery: Cervecería Cuauhtémoc Moctezuma S.A. de C.V.

name: Yeastie boys gunnamatta
desc: Amazingly floral but with so little bitterness. Has a slight spicyness as well which balances perfectly

name: Tortured gum capital pale ale
desc: A little tangy for a pale but still nice. Though on further tasting I've found some bottles to be a little bit too tangy and tastes more like an imperfection than a feature

name: Little creatures dog days
desc: Surprisingly flavourful for a summer beer. Nice little tang to it

name: Tradewind lager
desc: Easy drinking lager. Good for an all day drink

name: Big shed Kol schisel
desc: Fairly plain and easy drinking

name: Tortured gum stinger
desc: kind of tart but sits in a strange place like it can't decide what to be

name: Bristol beer factory independence
desc: The description sounded good but didn't quite hit that mark

name: HopDog cosmic highway
desc: Well named, you can't quite pick what you're drinking. Not bad but fails to master any category

name: Palm hop select
desc: I expected more, there's a slight metallic taste which shouldn't be in a nice beer

name: Riverside othello's curse
desc: Too harsh on the tongue. The one time I've wanted a smaller bottle

name: Abita jockamo
desc: Too harsh, this brewery is still yet to win me over

name: Brontide smooth black ale
desc: Started off a bit harsh but was a lot better than other black ales. Makes me want to try more dark beers

name: Rodenbach
desc: Surprisingly tangy with very little bitterness. Worth a try

name: Weihenstephaner pils
desc: Refreshing but not my favourite flavour

name: Shepherd Neame IPA
desc: I’m always disappointed by English IPAs since the flavour I want from an IPA is more akin to the American interpretation with much more floral hops

name: Red horse beer
desc: Nicer than expected. Has a slightly spicy finish

name: Bridge road little bling
desc: Not tasty enough to justify the low alcohol

name: Molson Canadian
desc: Crisp and refreshing but nothing special

name: Yeasty boys hud-a-wa strong
desc: An interestingly strong flavour but it maintains a smooth finish

name: Blackfont kölsch
desc: I love a good kolsch. So easy drinking but without being flavourless

name: Blackfont copper ale
desc: The final sip of this beer made me sad that it was gone

name: Batch big Paul's mango IPA
desc: The mango flavour doesn't overpower what is already a fantastic IPA

name: Willie the boatman Albo corn ale

name: Willie the boatman old salty gose

name: Belhaven Twisted Thistle IPA
desc: Started off with a bit of a tang but seemed to lose it towards the end

name: Mornington brown
desc: Nicely rounded. Another winner from Mornington

name: Mountain goat pale ale
desc: Really refreshing with the right amount of hop flavour for a pale ale

name: James Squire Swindler
desc: Disappointingly plain

name: Mountain goat hightail ale
desc: Still yet to have a bad beer from mountain goat though they are a bit too similar

name: Karl Strauss Tower 10 IPA
desc: An IPA with a sweet finish

name: Belhaven scottish ale
desc: Scottish ale isn’t one of my favourite styles so I can’t give it a top rating

name: Fóti
desc: Has a really mild ginger taste. The smell is a little strange but the flavour really grows on you

name: Brabante trigo
desc: Surprisingly this cheap beer is one of the better wheat beers that I’ve had. The tang is really well balanced. That said it is a bit light on flavour

name: Westvleteren Blond
desc: A lot lighter on flavour than I expected but then the bottle I have is older than it should be. That said it is perfectly balanced down to the last drop and there’s a hint of some deliciousness there. Not worth the price you pay in this country but I would love to get a fresh case of this

name: Anchor IPA
desc: I can’t enjoy this while eating. The bitterness difference is just too large for my taste buds to cope. Outside of that the bitterness is still a little too strong for the hop aroma

name: Brew dog Jack Hammer
desc: So much floral and citrus aroma. More bitterness than I would like but once you get used to it the flavour is amazing

name: Yeastie Boys Dark Matta
desc: Pretty good for a dark beer. Fairly smooth and rich but perhaps a little too bitter

name: Masters Finest
desc: No flavour except some bitterness

name: Pirate life Throwback IPA
desc: Great smell but a bit lacking on flavour. A nice session IPA

name: Vilkmergės kvietinis
desc: Pretty standard wheat beer

name: Houblon Chouffe Double IPA Triple
desc: Doesn’t really taste much like an IPA, nor is it the best Belgian blonde

name: Lupulus Pale ale
desc: Fantastically flavoured pale ale. Still mild though

name: Dogfish head indian brown ale
desc: One of the nicer browns I’ve had

name: Pirate Life Imperial IPA
desc: Hugely fragrant and really tasty

name: Dogfish head 90 minute IIPA
desc: Really nice flavour. Solid beer all the way

name: Forester bitter amber ale
desc: A little sour but not in a bad way

name: Emelisse rye smoked IPA
desc: To me the smokiness gives it some harshness that I don’t like

name: Pirate Life Pale Ale
desc: Had more flavour than anticipated, it’s actually a lot like the IIPA but with less bitterness

name: Hop Federation Pale ale
desc: Don’t have the best memory of drinking this but it was ok

name: Rockpool Pilsner
desc: Crisp but ultimately flavourless. Perhaps I've been having too many IPAs recently

name: Hawthorn IPA
desc: Delicious. A little bitter but lots of hoppy flavour

desc: Overly bitter and without much malt flavour. Still yet to find a great amber

name: Mornington Imperial Amber

name: Snow

name: Akasha freshwater pale ale
desc: Mild on hops but also low on bitterness

name: Queen’s Ale Extra Bitter Type
desc: It’s bitter and a little malty

name: Weidmann
desc: A little bit more malty than most German lagers

name: Queen’s Ale Blonde Type
desc: Supposed to be hoppy but it’s just bitter. Feels like it’s missing something

name: Sierra Nevada Rye IPA
desc: Smells really good but the taste is a little harsh

name: Cucapa brown ale
desc: It’s not awful but I can’t really get into it

name: Sierra Nevada Celebration
desc: Not as fresh as I was hoping but still nice

name: Jelen pivo
desc: Has a strange smell and a kind of malty taste

name: Six strings pale ale
desc: The bitterness is a tad too harsh but it’s nicely hopped

name: Lav
desc: Standard malty european cheap lager

name: Skorubrew #2 Pale Ale
desc: Has a bit of a yeasty smell but it’s covered up a bit by a mild hop aroma. Low on bitterness with a bit of sweetness and not too malty. All round quite drinkable

name: Duel Hoppy Lager
desc: Nicer than I expected, quite a bit of hop aroma coming off this and a well rounded taste

name: 8bit
desc: Really nice IPA, little strong but a good hop profile

name: Chop shop pale ale

name: Mornington why so cereal
desc: Really nice. Not too strong on flavour but well balanced. Give it a go if you're new to pale ales

name: Yulli's seabass
desc: Can't pick what the flavour is but I like it. Not as plain as I was expecting

name: Gage roads sleeping giant
desc: Very little hop flavour, mostly just bitterness. Somewhere underneath there’s a nice flavour trying to break through

name: Deschutes mirror pond pale ale
desc: Could be a little hoppier but it's still smooth and sweet with a nice hint of caramel

name: Mont Blanc Génépi
desc: Kind of tastes how it looks. Like a like cordial mixed with beer. The little bit of spice ties it together and makes for a nice sweet beer

name: Evil twin Falco
desc: A little more bitter than I was hoping but has a nice hop finish

name: Deschutes fresh squeezed IPA
desc: Really citrusy, a little too bitter but still a great drink

name: Liger
desc: Fizzy and dark and sweet

name: Tuatara Ardennes
desc: The Belgian flavour makes it taste stronger than it is. It’s fairly good but there are so many better Belgian beers out there that it’s not doing enough to bring me back

name: Panhead APA
desc: Interesting smell but the taste is covered up too much by the bitterness

name: Skorubrew #3
desc: Pretty good all round. Has a nice sweetness which balances well against the slight citrus hop profile

name: Beirut beer
desc: Tastes like a cheap Eastern European beer

name: Pirate life Hopco NZ pale ale
desc: Doesn’t have the same floral taste that their other beers have. It’s still hoppy but more of the bitterness is coming through

name: Stone coffee milk stout
desc: Creamy, rich and oh so dark. The coffee flavour is mild enough for me to enjoy

name: Golden road ride on IPA
desc: Huge floral hop aroma. Perhaps just a tad too bitter but very enjoyable

name: Pirate Life IPA
desc: Another great beer from Pirate Life. Nicely hoppy

name: Delirium Argentum
desc: Had a slightly metallic taste to start but otherwise it’s a really clean and crisp beer. Much milder in taste than other Belgian beers. I’m beginning to get the feeling that Belgian IPAs don’t have the hop profile that I expect

name: Wayward brewing rose kölsch
desc: Great kölsch. Crisp and clean but keeps you coming back

name: Prickly Moses harvest ale
desc: Pretty plain ale

name: Holgate Norton lager
desc: A very sweet lager with much more flavour than your average lager

name: Skorubrew stout #4

name: Batch smoking Russian party guy
desc: Quite mild on the stout flavour, sweet and tasty

name: Batch American pale ale
desc: Pretty good pale ale. Nothing super exciting

name: Batch in a pickle
desc: My first cucumber beer. Tastes a lot like pickles. It's interesting but it wouldn't bring me back

name: Batch seeing red IRA
desc: Pretty much a red IPA. Nice flavour but doesn't have as much floral aroma as I like

name: Grifter Marnie's majority ale
desc: Nicely floral, not too bitter. All round good IPA

name: Grifter big sur
desc: Strong on flavour, big on hops

name: Shenanigans flight path
desc: Smells like and IPA, tastes like a stout. But still pretty good

name: XX bitter
desc: Not as hoppy as the label indicates,  almost European in the maltyness

name: Riverside brewing 88 robust porter
desc: One of the less sweet porters I’ve had but still not bitter. Not my favourite

name: Dad & Dave’s Pale ale #1
desc: Tastes like a Belgian ale. It’s alright

name: Dad & Dave’s Belgian IPA #2
desc: Like other Belgian IPAs it’s not very hoppy

name: Dad & Dave’s Pils #3
desc: Pretty good pilsner

name: Beachwood road dark harvest
desc: Smells hoppy but tastes stouty

name: Akasha fire within
desc: Pretty spot on for what I expect from an amber ale but doesn't have a flavour I love

name: Derwent aromatic spelt ale

name: Grifter Serpents kiss
desc: The slight watermelon taste makes it hard to enjoy the beer. You get used to it but there's not a lot of reason to

name: Dark knight porter style
desc: Mild and sweet. Nice easy drinking porter

name: Feral karma citra
desc: A little bit too stouty and bitter for me but otherwise good

name: Moo brew single hop
desc: A little bit lacking on the hop side but well rounded. Kind of want to know what hop and malt they use

name: Brabante lager
desc: Pretty plain lager, slightly better than your standard Australian beers

name: Stone IPA
desc: Very bitter and lacking in hops but ok

name: Akasha water buffalo
desc: Has a few flavours which are hard to pin down but it works well. Has a nice amount of sweetness

name: Arc Valley Lager
desc: Nothing particularly good about this beer. It’s drinkable but that’s about it

name: Namysrów pils
desc: Malty European pils. Nothing special

name: Sierra Nevada Otra vez
desc: Smells strange bad but tastes completely different. Having trouble describing exactly what I’m getting here, kind of like watermelon. Perhaps too many things going on all at once. I wouldn’t want many but it’s worth the experience

name: Magic rock Cannonball IPA
desc: Has the floral smell that I love in an IPA and a nice balance of bitterness and hops. A great example of an IPA

name: Exit milk stout
desc: Not nearly as sweet as I expected, almost had a sour note. Once I got used to it it was an enjoyable drink

name: The continuous daryl
desc: One amazing beer. Spot on with bitterness and fruitiness

name: Holgate temptress
desc: A little bit too bitter and too stouty for me. Not getting any chocolate either

name: Magic rock high wire grapefruit
desc: Fruity like a soft drink but still bitter like a beer. Smells a little bit like past. Different and refreshing

name: Holgate hop tart
desc: An interesting beer. Could do with a little more hop flavour to go with the sourness but refreshing as it is

name: Rogue dead guy
desc: Like a really sweet IPA. There’s something else in there that I can’t put my finger on

name: Skorubrew #6
desc: A little underwhelmed with the hop flavour, it didn’t come out as strong as I expected. While I wouldn’t really call this an IPA it’s still a nice beer. Not too bitter and really easy to drink

name: Magic rock salty kiss
desc: Fairly mild on flavour. Easy to drink and refreshing

name: Tuatara outrigger
desc: More of a Belgian flavour than I expected. Ok but not great

name: Legal tender
desc: Has a slightly sweet taste and a spicy finish. Drink it quick before it gets warm

name: Lord Nelson dead ahead
desc: There's an interesting background flavour, perhaps honey, but it's overwhelmed by the bitterness. A little disappointing

name: Skorubrew #5
desc: Definitely tastes like a belgian ale. Not the favourite beer I've made but it's ok

name: Skorubrew #7
desc: There’s a slight caramel/toffee flavour that comes through but the apple isn’t there except for the smell. More bitter than my other beers but it’s not overwhelming

name: Skorubrew #8
desc: A much more in your face stout than my #3. The chocolate hasn’t come through but the sweetness from the lactose has. There’s a noticeable coffee flavour as well that I didn’t expect. Amazingly though it comes together really well and is quite easy drinking

name: Six strings dark red IPA
desc: Too much bitterness overwhelming the other flavours

name: Cleanskin Green beer
desc: Not as cheap tasting as I expected. Low bitterness and a sweet malt profile make it fairly drinkable

name: Yenda Hell
desc: Almost tasteless. Absolutely nothing exciting about this beer

name: Barossa brewing I can't believe it's not bacon
desc: Super smokey but not overwhelming. Definitely evokes memories of bacon

name: West end draught
desc: Uninspired south Australian lager. Not as bitter as other Australian brews but there's no hops or malt to make it s decent beer

name: Barossa valley hop heaven
desc: Nicely balanced hops. Bitterness is on par for what I expect from a beer like this. Great smell too

name: Barossa valley SA wit
desc: Really refreshing. Would go great on a hot day. One of the better wit beers I've had

name: Clare valley bulls eye
desc: Overly bitter with no hop profile

name: Prancing pony sunshine ale
desc: A little bit lacking but not a bad beer

name: Clare valley monkey's uncle
desc: Another bitter beer but tastes like a red ale. Decent flavours behind the bitterness

name: Malt fiction session ale

name: Magic hat smash hits IPA
desc: Definitely an IPA but not terribly nice. Surprisingly the bitterness went away as it got warmer and it was a bit nicer

name: Magic hat Stealin time
desc: Really nice ginger hit

name: Mornington dogs bollocks
desc: Oh so smooth. One of easiest drinking beers I’ve ever had

name: Innes & Gunn fired oak scotch ale
desc: You can really taste the oak flavours coming through Has a slightly strange flavour but overall pretty nice

name: James squire hop thief #8
desc: Didn’t think I would enjoy this one as much as the #7 given the hops but it’s just as good

name: Steam whistle pilsner
desc: Easy drinking. Fairly dry and not too bitter

name: Mismatch Extra pale ale
desc: Really tasty brew. Not as bitter as I expected which works well with mild hop flavour

name: Shark island pale ale
desc: My first from this brewery, happy so far. Mild on hops but the sweetness from the malt holds it together

name: Shark island summer ale
desc: A little bit too yeasty. Not what I expect from a summer ale

name: Blackfont Belgian pale ale
desc: Perfect example of a Belgian

name: Blackfont saison de Ville
desc: The best saison I've had. Like drinking a piece of fruit

name: Batch juicy as phuck dark
desc: So much hop aroma with no bitterness. A style I've been searching for but it could be more balanced

name: Batch tank 6 imperial stout
desc: There's a beautiful flavour but it's hidden behind some harshness which slightly spoils it

name: Feral smoked porter
desc: Smooth but without the backing to make it a great beer

name: Hotchkiss six
desc: Really mild easy drinking stout. Kind of lacks any interesting depth of flavour

name: Anderson valley blood orange gose
desc: Takes a bit of getting used to, orange doesn’t usually go with salty. Not something I would buy again

name: Redbay bearded hobo pale ale
desc: Crisp and dry. Very easy drinking, a great pale ale for someone new to beer

name: Redbay Vlad White IPA
desc: The hops cut through what I normally dislike in a wheat beer. Nicely aromatic and not too bitter

name: Redbay Black gold coffee porter
desc: A nice balance between beer and coffee. Could do with some more sweetness

name: Liebenweiss hefe weissbier
desc: Really citrusy which hides the yeastiness

name: Destroy all humans
desc: Tastes like it wants to kill me. Was this even supposed to be consumed?

name: Willie smith triple
desc: Super strange color but with an amazing taste. Starts with a kick then followed by a mild berry sweetness which then mellows out for a smooth finish

name: Anderson Valley Hop Ottin IPA
desc: Super flavourful. Initially it’s very bitter but once you get over that it’s amazing. It’s exactly what I expect when a beer says it’s an IPA. Not to mention it just looks beautiful in a glass. If you see it try it out

name: Merchant Hasselsloth west coast IPA
desc: After the IPA I just had this seems a bit tasteless. It’s not bad in any way it’s just that I had already been spoiled somewhat during the evening. The name is of course what drew me in and can’t be faulted but the beer isn’t as flavourful as I would like

name: Little brewing death between the tanks DIPA
desc: After having 2 IPAs this was the perfect follow on. My palate was fully ready to ignore the 113 IBUs and delve into the flavours beneath. It’s full of citrusy hops which give you fruitiness but with the undeniable awareness that this is a strong beer. As I finish my glass I look at the bottom with sadness that I have no more of this supreme liquid, I’m left only with the hoppy smell of the bottle and the realisation that the next beer will not be as good

name: Magic hat poppy agave ale
desc: Not terribly exciting. The agave seems to smooth it out a bit but not enough to really differentiate it

name: Basement brew house American pale ale
desc: Has a nice balance between IPA bitterness and the easy drinking of a pale. It's not special but it's a crowd pleaser

name: Basement brew house sparkling
desc: Strong on galaxy hops, low on bitterness. Really easy drinking but in no way plain

name: Yulli's fat nerd vanilla porter
desc: No question of the vanilla. The sweetness makes it a really nice porter but by the end of a pint it felt like a bit much. Would only recommend ordering a middy

name: Wayward Keller instinct
desc: Has a really strange flavour in the back. Interesting as something I've not had before but not going to bring me back

name: White rabbit barrel aged red
desc: An interesting style. Kind of a half sour beer.  Hints of cherry. Worth a look if you want something new

name: Brewcult get down American brown
desc: More of a stout than a brown due to the lack of sweetness. Kind of disappointing

name: Wayward Pine-a-pils
desc: Nice hoppiness but theres a harshness to it that detracts a little bit

name: Wayward smokin aces
desc: The smokiness enhances the bitterness without adding much

name: Wayward saison
desc: Nice level of yeast flavour vs sweetness. Makes me not hate saisons

name: Wayward  fusami
desc: Ok, but a little mild. For some reason I thought it was an IPA not a lager

name: Stone & wood garden ale
desc: A little lacking in flavour but easily drinkable

name: 4 pines hoppy dobblebock
desc: Not really my cup of tea. The flavours just don’t seem to work well together

name: Phoenix beer
desc: Quite a dry beer. Nothing exciting or worth looking for

name: Brewdog Jet Black Heart
desc: Reminds me of drinking in Shoreditch. Initially lots of coffee and chocolate but then a slight milkiness. Easy drinking and also lots of flavour

name: FoxHat metric IPA
desc: Given the 80 IBU it’s amazing how smooth and easy drinking this beer is. Great to see a west coast IPA which strives for balance over just packing in hops

name: Brewdog Ace of Simcoe
desc: I love the smell and the floral side of the hops but there’s a harsh bitterness that’s out of place. It’s a decent IPA but there’s nothing amazing going on

name: Boatrocker hop bomb IPA
desc: Definitely a lot of hops but the heavy use of earthy hops leaves it bitter but without any exciting flavours. My first from this brewery so hopefully the rest of their range is a bit better

name: Skorubrew #13 rice ale
desc: Smells citrusy and yeasty, the yeasty smell probably being the biggest let down. Has a sweet and very mild taste. A very refreshing and easy drinking beer. Also it just look beautiful

name: Oskar blues pinner
desc: Amazingly crisp smell of passionfruit coming through. Doesn’t carry through as much in the taste but it’s still there. There’s a bitterness too but it’s nicely balanced and overall delicious. This beer delivers everything it says on the can

name: Skorubrew #9 Pale ale
desc: A little over carbonated with no head retention but still a tasty drop. Fairly easy drinking with just a mild hop flavour. Has a sweet finish that takes away the bitterness

name: Boatrocker tripel
desc: Has a lovely nice yeasty aroma. There’s a rich warming sensation as you drink combined with a rich full flavour that is exactly what I expect from a tripel. Absolutely no harshness despite the high percentage and barely any perceptible bitterness

name: Mornington hop culture
desc: Lots of flavour given that it’s a session IPA. Seemed a little too bitter at first but once you get used to that it’s easy drinking. More earthy than floral but well balanced

name: Shenanigans malt assault
desc: One of the better smoked beers that I've had due. From the first sip one of the strangest beers I've had but it definitely got better. By the end the smokiness was less evident and I could enjoy the multitude of other flavours

name: Brewdog elvis juice
desc: The flavours aren't quite coming together on this one. The smell works but there's just too much bitterness from the grapefruit

name: Fox hat lusty lager
desc: Like taking a regular lager and boosting it in every way. Stronger, more flavour and less harshness. Good for enjoying at a moderate pace

name: Nomad freshie salt & pepper
desc: One of the better beers from nomad. Just a slight saltiness but mostly just a refreshing beer

name: Fix
desc: Better than expected. Has that malty Eastern European taste but there’s a little bit of a tang which rounds it off nicely

name: Willie the boatman nectar of the hops
desc: Just the beer I've been looking for. Barely any bitterness but full of hop flavours. Smell is all pine and floral. Not getting the juiciness promised but decent as an IPA

name: Skorubrew #14 belgian apple ale
desc: Really rounded flavour. Much less hoppy than my other brews and the slight apple tang adds something that you wouldn’t normally see. The high ABV adds another element. Overall a decent and unique beer

name: Big wave golden ale
desc: Very refreshing. Has a slight creaminess

name: 4 pines Indian summer ale
desc: Refreshing and easy drinking. Low bitterness, not much in the way of hops but enough to make it tasty

name: Akasha Korban DIPA
desc: It's what it says it is so I can't complain but there's a mildness that leaves me wanting.  Neither a great hop profile nor a punch in the face. Perhaps if I got a pint it would have been better

name: Golden road gingerbread stout
desc: You can really taste the gingerbread. There's also a lot of stoutiness. Can't say I would buy another but it's very interesting

name: Pirate life golden era
desc: Nicely aromatic. Easy drinking. The mildest beer I've had from the pirate life range

name: Alesmith IPA
desc: Has a bitterness that never really resolves into a great flavour

name: Hope black IPA
desc: Not too bad. The bitterness sits well with the slight stoutiness

name: Fixation IPA
desc: Really floral hop profile. Not nearly as big as I expected from the description but it's a nice balance that I could drink a few of

name: Boatrocker alpha queen
desc: Kind of a mix between an IPA and a pale. Low on bitterness but high on hops. Great as a session beer

name: Imperial
desc: Fairly plain lager. I don't want another

name: Mornington porter
desc: A good beer to enjoy slowly. Unmistakably a porter but it all fits together well

name: Rochefort 10
desc: It's been a while since I've had a beer that takes so long to get used to but continues to get better. Still can't say I love it but I would love to have more to continue to tease out the flavours

name: Westmalle triple
desc: Pretty good tipple this triple is. Easy drinking, nice and rounded. Slight spiciness. All the things I love

name: Devils daughters
desc: Decent aroma but lacks flavour. Doesn't qualify as a double IPA but still decent. Too many cheap hops I think

name: Katoomba brewing great white fleet
desc: Not the greatest pale. Just not the hops for me. But it's not offensive

name: Spiced pumpkin ale
desc: Has the pumpkin spice taste but the aftertaste has something confusing that slightly ruins it

name: Fox hat phat mongrel
desc: Low bitterness and the oats add a lot of smoothness. Worth trying even if you're not a fan of stouts. As it goes down the creaminess becomes more evident

name: Feral war hog
desc: Really nice smell and color but the taste doesn't meet my expectations. Too resiny and bitter. Gets better but it's too late

name: Modus operandi sonic prayer
desc: Surprisingly low of aroma but big on taste. Bitter to start but great to finish. Need to get more into this brewery

name: 4 pines guava gose
desc: Perfectly on par with what I expect. Salty and sour with some lingering flavour.  Not a great refreshing summer beer but good as a slow drink

name: Oskar blues IPA
desc: Pretty good piney kind of IPA. No depth to it though

name: Skorubrew #16
desc: Very much a Belgian ale. Not too bitter and very low on hop flavour. Not very pretty. Probably a good winter beer, sadly I brewed it in the summer

name: AC/DC Premium Lager
desc: A fairly plain and easy drinking beer. Giving it an extra point because of the sheer size of it. Managed to get through the whole thing in one sitting

name: DAX
desc: A little malty but really low compared to other euro lagers. Mostly just tastes like water

name: Nomad long reef pale ale
desc: Too bitter for a pale ale. It's decently balanced but the hop profile is a bit bland

name: Anderson valley holy gose
desc: Perfectly balances the salt,sour and sweetness to hit that gose sweet spot. Unfortunately I was in a bit of a rush so I had to slam this down, and while it is refreshing it also has enough flavour to make that difficult so I may have enjoyed this less than I could have

name: Mornington lager
desc: Very easy drinking. Would be great for getting pissed. Can't complain

name: Shenanigans gone troppo
desc: Tropical smell but not too strong. They've managed to get a lot of tropical flavour in there as well. Still had the bitterness of an IPA but it's not overwhelming. All round a delicious beer that delivers what it promises

name: Stockade wanderer märzen
desc: Strange and a little tangy. Smells a bit sour. Very little hop flavour or aroma, kind of sits in an odd spot between quaffable and flavourful brews. Pretty good with food

name: XXXX summer bright lager
desc: As it warms up it gets a real wheaty malt flavour. Mostly just a plain lager

name: Coopers limited edition brew A, IPA
desc: Pretty flavourless IPA. Was expecting more from coopers

name: Liberty brewing citra DIPA
desc: Has a really strange tang, not bad, just unexpected. Probably a tad too bitter for the amount of flavour packed in. Could be that I just ate a steak and a whole cob loaf and didn't have the space in my stomach left

name: Hawkers IPA
desc: Fairly well rounded, not too bitter. Easy drinking for an IPA and the ABV. More pine than floral with the hops but it woks well

name: Baladin Isaac
desc: One of the better wheat ales I've had. Almost no bitterness, really refreshing and just a little bit sweet. The wheat flavour is clearly there but not bothering me

name: Fox hat red pelt
desc: Feels like it's missing something. The bitterness is there but sadly no great flavour behind that. Really high levels of sediment as well. A rare miss from fox hat

name: Belching beaver peanut butter stout
desc: Can't pick out the peanut butter but there's a great smoothness that comes with it. Kind of wish they just called it a stout and didn't get my hopes up

name: Doctors orders tonic witbeer
desc: Very refreshing which is exactly what I need on a 40C day. Certainly has a taste of tonic, in a good way. I'm torn between loving this as an easy drinking beer and missing more interesting flavours

name: Skorubrew #18
desc: Has a beautiful hazy golden color. Starts off a bit yeasty but that fades quickly. Almost no lingering bitterness and there's a slight tangy flavour but there's just too something that seems wrong

name: Brewdog hop fiction pale ale
desc: A tad harsh but a decent floral aroma. Just the right level of flavour for a pale ale to be interesting and easily sessionable. Sadly I only have the 1

name: To Øl wit or witout
desc: A balance between a wit and a sour but perhaps too bitter to sit in that range. Fairly easy drinking but not as refreshing as I was hoping. Hard to pick out any flavours

name: Skorubrew #17
desc: My saison dry hopped with lemon grass. Has an interesting little tang to it. Has much less of a Belgian flavour than the #16 and is more rounded. Still more of a slow drinking winter beer than a refreshing saison

name: Wild yak pacific ale
desc: Easy drinking but with enough flavour to keep me happy

name: Koshihikari echigo
desc: It's decent, slightly better than I expected. Not too much hop forward flavour. Going well with dinner

name: Modus operandi session IPA
desc: Sweet drinking. Probably a little bit too drunk to fully appreciate this

name: Kalnapils pilsner
desc: I'm hungover and right now this is a massive help. Super easy drinking and right on point for a pilsner

name: Golden road wolf mother triple IPA
desc: Surprisingly smooth. Not actually that bitter. It's amazing when you can knock off this amount of booze and still feel like it's a fresh beer

name: Beer of the dead porter
desc: A sweet smell with a mild stoutiness. Not super exciting but on point for what is and easy to drink
brewery: Cervecería Mexicana S. de R.L. de C.V. (Tecate)

name: Golden road saison citron
desc: A little bit too heavy on the farmhouse sharpness for me

name: Extra hop sauce
desc: Medium bitterness and heavy on earthy hops. Good middle of the road IPA

name: Young Henry's mulberia
desc: Interesting colour, I expected it to be a little more sour. It's mild and easy drinking but sits in a place that's not quite my thing

name: Willie the boatman salty melon
desc: Once you get past the salt there's a touch of melon. The only issue is the more you drink the thirstier your get. But it delivers everything it promises

name: Australian new world pilsner
desc: A little too dry for my liking

name: La Sirène praline
desc: Like Nutella in beer form but also not at all. Nutty, chocolaty, smooth and oh so dark. Rather filling for a beer which makes me happy with one despite it being a tasty beer

name: Newstead two to the valley
desc: Not sure what's in this IPA but it's all wrong. Like really difficult to drink

name: Beer of the dead hop on or die
desc: I don’t think my cat isn’t too happy about being used as a prop. There’s a nice warmingness but it goes down pretty easy. No great hoppyness but it’s well balanced
brewery: Cervecería Mexicana S. de R.L. de C.V. (Tecate)

name: Stelle and Strisce
desc: One of the most over carbonated beers I’ve found. Took forever for the head to reach drinkable levels. Smells of some slightly funky yeast and that carries though to the taste but the flavour is mild otherwise. It’s in a spot where it’s almost amazing but doesn’t quite manage to get there

name: Buxton Pic Tor
desc: Unfortunately this beer has a sourness that just tastes off. Like rotten fruit or beer mixed with shit wine

name: Balter XPA
desc: A nice bit of hops with low bitterness. I've never been a fan of XPAs before but I really see how this works as a style. Also the can is smiling at me

name: Skorubrew #19 red rye IPA
desc: A little darker than I planned but still red. Has a yeasty, Belgian smell which fades and lets the smokiness through. But the hero here is the taste. The smoked malt and rye add an element that you don’t normally find. The lower bitterness means this flavour doesn’t linger which keeps you wanting more. The Belgian yeast rounds the flavour further and the 7.5% gives a slight warming sensation. My best homebrew yet

name: Wrong side brewing pale ale
desc: A little biscuity but otherwise a pretty plain and tasteless beer

name: Brew by numbers Belgian pale
desc: Mild for a Belgian ale which makes it easy drinking but also leaves me wanting more. And I mean more in the beer, not wanting another. Not that I would complain

name: Boatrocker pale ale
desc: Has a weird after taste that doesn't belong in this beer. There's something interesting as well but altogether it doesn't quite work

name: Batch trippy hippy citra xpa
desc: Piney but lacking citrus to round it out. Gets better as I drink but it almost has a wheat flavour which I wasn't what I was hoping for

name: Doctors orders saccharophobic
desc: Not as much caramel as I hoped. It's definitely there but you have to search. It's an easy drinking brown with a little bit extra and I wish I had some more

name: Yeastie boys bigmouth
desc: Fairly sessionable but not as good as other things I've had from them. But perhaps I've just hit the point where I've had enough beer for the night

name: Carling black label
desc: Fairly dry with a little hint of malt in the back. A little stronger than most lagers which is nice. Easy drinking but it’s not an exciting beer

name: 4 pines Keller door hop hash XPA
desc: Nice selection of hops. Perhaps just a little too harsh for my liking but still easy drinking and full of flavour. Feel like I could drink a lot of these

name: Pirate life white labs pilsner
desc: Has a really lovely spicyness which gives this beer a little more flavour than a regular pilsner. Still easy drinking and smooth but with enough depth to keep me happy

name: Viven Master IPA
desc: Not really what I expect from an IPA but that’s normal for a Belgian IPA. I’m torn between this being an easy and balanced drink and it lacking exciting flavours. There’s a little bit of spiciness as it warms at least

name: Castle lager
desc: It’s lager. Nothing much else to say

name: Newsteads wastelands red rye IPA
desc: Really loving rye in beers lately where it’s not overwhelming. Because this isn’t a hoppy beer it’s still the hero

name: Dam burg
desc: Lager with a slightly richer level of malt than normal

name: Kaiju! Hopped out red
desc: Has a really deep flavour. The earthy hops are there but they don’t take away from this being a red ale. Overall it’s really well balanced and easy drinking

name: Kaiju! Metamorphosis IPA
desc: Too heavy on the bitterness for my liking and quite piney and resiny. Having a couple would be nice to give me more time to get used to it and pick out the hop flavours over the bitterness

name: Kaiju! robohop
desc: Heavy and full of flavour. Good mix of hops in the middle of floral and earthy . High starting bitterness but it doesn't linger

name: La Sirène Urban Pale
desc: Straight away has a saison yeasty tang. More restrained on the hops than I expected from a pale. Light, refreshing and easy to drink, just not what I expected

name: Del Borgo Prunus
desc: The colour is absolutely beautiful. Smells funky as hell but the taste is much better. Full of a sour fruitiness and reminds me of plums but doesn’t have any off flavours. There’s almost no bitterness and a subtle sweetness to finish

name: Colonial draught Kölsch
desc: A great refreshing beer. Malt driven but not to the level of European lagers. Exactly what I expect from a kölsch

name: Liberty brewing yakima monster
desc: Resiny and citrus hops. It could almost be an IPA given the ABV and amount of hops. Fairly well rounded overall and the more I drink the more I wish I had another one

name: Ridgeway IPA
desc: Has a mild Belgian yeastiness. Not at all what I expect from an IPA but it’s enjoyable nonetheless. Mild and easy drinking with a slight taste of hops

name: Ballast point even keel
desc: A lot of flavour for a small beer. Tastes very much like a west coast IPA. My main complaint is that while the bitterness and hops are there the mouthfeel is a bit watery so it doesn’t have the a nice smoothness. Worth a try but I wouldn’t be looking for another

name: Nomad Rosie’s summer punch
desc: I think this is the best berliner weisse I’ve found. Really refreshing and easy drinking with just a slight sourness

name: Oskar blues beerito
desc: Expected something light and tasteless. It’s actually quite malty and full of flavour. Still not exciting enough to bring me back

name: Skorubrew #20 witbier
desc: Love the colour I got with this one but not much else. A really yeast driven beer and perhaps too much for my taste

name: Newstead 21 feet 7 inches
desc: Such a smooth dark beer. Dominated by a rich coffee flavour. I don’t even like coffee but I like this. Not much malt going on. Fairly light on the sweetness but the bitterness also so that’s balances out for me

name: Wrong side brewing Raspberry pale
desc: Definitely has a raspberry flavour in there but fairly mild otherwise. Not sour like you might expect from a fruit beer. Interesting concept but could do with some hops to balance the sweetness

name: Kaiju! crush
desc: I’ve been dying to try out this beer. The hops are all floral and citrus but without any of the bitterness that normally comes with such a hoppy beer. It manages to be refreshing while still packing in tons of flavour. Reminds me a lot of the pirate life pale ale

name: Big shed golden stout time
desc: Smells like vanilla and cookies, so much so that the initial bitterness is a shock. Seems like an attempt to mix the flavours of an ice cream with beer, which is obviously difficult so it’s a complex beer that just manages to hold together

name: Moondog splice of heaven
desc: The bottle kicked off the experience by frothing all over the table. Definitely smells like lime but I can’t taste it

name: Valhalla Ziggy
desc: Really easy drinking for a red ale, mellow as hell. Usually I love big beers full of flavour but this is a perfect easy drinking craft beer

name: Hope DIPA
desc: All pine and floral on the nose. A little resiny in taste but not to the point where it overbalances the other flavours. Definitely a hop forward bitter DIPA

name: Mount pleasant shake your fruity milkshake
desc: Clear but full of particles. There's something odd in this beer, not bad just a flavour I can't pick out. Bitterness is completely overshadowed by the hops, just how I like my IPA

name: Modus operandi pale ale
desc: A little more bitter than expected. But there's a delicious sweetness that works well. It's moderately hoppy, somewhere in the middle between easy drinking and flavourful

name: Bridge side cut
desc: Loving the haze on this beer. Full of floral and citrus hops with a little bit of pine. It's biter but it balances perfectly. Full of flavour but I could drink a bunch of these

name: Jerkface 9000
desc: Not at all what I expected from something labeled as a wheat beer, more like a hoppy pale ale. But I can’t complain because it’s pretty damn good. Manages to be easy drinking at the same time. The kind of beer you could have bunch of

name: Tropical torpedo
desc: Starts off tropical with quite a bit of pineapple going on. But that fades and it has a bit of a Belgian spiciness which I wasn’t expecting. It’s good but I expected more

name: Oskar blues death by coconut
desc: Not as much coconut as I was expected from the name. I would say there’s actually more vanilla than coconut. It’s nicely smooth, but perhaps a little bit overly sweet. Interesting to try but I’m not rushing for another

name: Feral brewing tusk
desc: Has a bitterness but it doesn't linger at all. Lots of fresh citrus hops making this full of flavour. Would never guess this has as much alcohol as it does, it's dangerously easy to drink

name: Beer creative Einstein
desc: Mostly malt driven. A little bit of a roasted flavour. It's decent but not that exciting, quite easy to drink though

name: Shenanigans hoppy Gonzales
desc: Straight away you get the jalapeño but it's only the taste and no heat. Fairly hoppy on the nose but it's hard to pick that up in the taste

name: 4 pines nitro stout
desc: Looks a lot like a Guinness but it's not as dry so easier to drink. No strong flavours but a decent session beer

name: Mismatch extra pale ale
desc: Quite strong for an XPA but I'm not complaining because it's pretty tasty. Good balance between bitterness and hop aromatics. A nice mix of resiny and fruity

name: Sierra Nevada Sidecar
desc: Very orange in color, smells a little like an unpeeled orange but it doesn’t really carry through to the flavour. I like the idea but it doesn’t come together that well

name: Four winds Nectarous
desc: I can’t pick out any of the dry hop flavours but I’m ok with that because it’s a delicious sour. The kind of sour which gets it right without bothering to worry about hiding it with fruit. It’s hard to say much about this because I don’t have much to compare it to. Definitely worth a try for anyone who feels like experimenting with sours

name: All star session IPA
desc: A little bitter with mostly earthy hops

name: Žatecky Gus
desc: Your basic flavourless lager except in a giant can. Just what I need right now

name: Doan amaretto
desc: Quite a lot going on but it's hard to pick out. Both a little smokey and quite creamy. There's a sweetness too but it doesn't fight with the other flavours

name: Feral Fanta pants
desc: Finally found a beer that lets me understand the dankness of an IPA. The bitterness is high but it’s well rounded. Seems a bit like it has many different styles of hops involved which all come together to give that dank

name: Dageraad Sri Lanka
desc: Definitely a Belgian ale but it’s hard to say if it’s anything more

name: Founders KBS
desc: Super packed with flavour. The bourbon comes through as well as a huge amount of toastyness. Can't taste the booze at all. Still not worth the price

name: Founders breakfast stout
desc: A nice easy drinking mild stout, pretty great example of what a stout should be

name: Doctors orders electrolyte serum
desc: Tastes more like a wheat ale than a gose. Not bad but I wanted more

name: Dos blockos fuck the rent
desc: Really flavourful golden ale full of malty goodness. Not a special beer but a decent staple

name: Kona pipeline
desc: Slightly watered down stout. Just doesn't have the creaminess that I want right now

name: Bacchus jaffacake ale
desc: A fairly thin dark ale. The chocolate and orange are fairly mild. Interesting but I probably didn't need a pint

name: Bacchus Lammingtonne
desc: You really get lamington as you swallow just without the sweetness. Powerful but easy drinking. Could have been a bit creamier

name: Bacchus hibiscus saison
desc: Looks like a feminine beer but it definitely isn't. Has a very strong Belgian taste to it. The hibiscus comes through as well. Doesn't have the freshness that I expected

name: Bacchus kraken IPA
desc: Pretty dank and tasty. The rum comes through but it's really faint

name: Bacchus sex drugs & rocky road
desc: Definitely evokes memories of rocky road but the bitterness overpowers a lot of it

name: Bucket boys This is rice country
desc: Very light. Has almost a slight spicyness

name: Grifter banshee
desc: Slight toastyness. Like a very thin stout. Easy drinking but lacks depth

name: Blackfont Brett fermented Belgian
desc: Full Belgian flavour but a bit lighter. Has a delicious lingering taste that I can't quite describe. Absolutely smooth with almost no bitterness

name: Blackfont wheat IPA
desc: Wheat is there but the hops are the hero. Still fairly light for an IPA and somehow the bitterness barely comes through

name: Blackfont Baltic porter
desc: Creamy for a Baltic and smooth for the strength. Fairly mild in flavour but really easy to drink

name: Blackfont imperial oatmeal stout
desc: Smooth and creamy with no bitterness but a little sour

name: Blackfont souvenir old ale
desc: Everything about this beer is amazing

name: Batch hopsy mozy nitro IPA
desc: Love the creamyness on this beer

name: Grifter demon lungs
desc: It's a good level of smoke but lacks much else

name: Grifter omen
desc: Good stout which causes no qualms but delivers nothing special

name: Grifter tavern ale
desc: My favourite of the range so far. Clean and crisp

name: Coal harbour Smoke & Mirrors
desc: Super smokey, in fact too much for the size of the bottle. It was smooth otherwise so there wasn't much to cover the smokiness

name: Mornington brain squeeze
desc: Classic Mornington quality. Slightly sour and easy drinking. A good all day beverage

name: Crafty dan 13 guns
desc: Decent hop aroma but it doesn't come through much in the taste. Fairly smooth for an IPA but it's not enough to save it

name: Goose island 312 urban wheat ale
desc: Mild in all possible ways but well balanced. The wheat is barely noticeable to the point where you could mistake this for a lager

name: Under current oatmeal pale ale
desc: Quite flavourful and full of hops. I like the haze but I wish it was a little creamier. Pretty good but misses its potential

name: Blue point toasted lager
desc: Fairly mild lager but with a little bit of something extra. Could be called an amber ale. Pretty solid all round

name: Curious Brew Lager
desc: Surprisingly malty but not much else going on. It was drinkable after already being rather smashed but I wouldn’t want another one

name: The kernel Loral IPA
desc: It's a strange hop. Kind of a pine and floral mix and something else I can't pinpoint

name: Goose IPA
desc: Fairly plain. A little too bitter for the hop level

name: The kernel centennial IPA
desc: It's a very ugly looking IPA. Initially very bitter but that faded. Mostly pine aroma but not much hop flavour coming through. It’s a decent IPA but doesn’t go further than that

name: The kernel simcoe pale ale
desc: Another fairly ugly beer, which may be the result of it being badly stored. On the nose it’s mostly citrus with a bit of spice. Full of flavour without being too bitter. Quality all round

name: Sadlers Land of liberty American IPA
desc: Looks and tastes nothing like an IPA. It somehow manages to be malt driven rather than hop driven. It’s not a bad beer but a complete fail for the style

name: Wimbledon copper leaf ale
desc: A rather mild real ale. Easy drinking but ultimately lacking flavour

name: Guinness hop house 13
desc: A nice hoppy lager. If you want a base lager with that little bit extra

name: Meantime pale ale
desc: Really nice sweetness balanced with the hops. But seems like it is more of an amber than a pale

name: Maes pils
desc: Pretty easy drinking, what you would expect from a pilsner

name: Blanche de Brugs
desc: Bang on for a witbeer. Starts out yeasty buy the lemon cuts through it. Really easy drinking and refreshing

name: Delirium red
desc: Expected an amber ale but got a cherry beer. Very easy drinking and refreshing without the fruit being too strong

name: Bersalis triple
desc: It's good but something just seems off about it. Gets better with time but never what I'm hoping for

name: Grimbergen triple
desc: A fairly light triple but the yeast just seems a bit off

name: Kasteel rouge
desc: Another cherry beer. Really need to learn what to expect from a rouge beer

name: Brussels beer project delta IPA
desc: The first Belgian IPA I’ve found that actually resembles an IPA. Not too bitter and moderately hoppy

name: Cantillon gueuze
desc: It's not as sour as I expected. Lots of really subtle flavours that take a while to get used to but it's an interesting experience

name: Cantillon lambic
desc: Flat and rather mild. Feels like a really old style that's hard to compare to normal beers. It's pleasant but not exciting

name: Vieux temps
desc: Easy drinking Belgian blonde with a slight malty finish

name: Westvleteren 12
desc: Really full of flavour. It's not harsh on the throat but gives a warming sensation. It's slightly tangy with a lot of candied sugar coming through. It's definitely a sipping beer but it's one you could stay on until you collapsed

name: Hopus
desc: Light and sweet with a mild yeastiness. Tastes like a session beer but packed with alcohol

name: Trappist Achel
desc: Comes off a little harsh. Ok but there are plenty of better Belgian beers
brewery: Brouwerij der Sint-Benedictusabdij de Achelse Kluis

name: Sion kölsch
desc: Malty, low on bitterness and easy drinking. Even Amy had one

name: Peters kölsch
desc: A little malty with a sweet finish. Very easy to go through but not exciting

name: Gaffel kölsch
desc: At first it seems like the malt is overwhelming but it's hiding a hint of spice

name: Jaws nuclear laundry
desc: Pretty decent hop punch with a nice dankness. Surprisingly easy to drink despite this

name: Stone xocoveza
desc: Has a very strange taste. Apart from the bitterness it’s not much like a beer at all. It’s pretty good but not something I would go back for

name: Heiden Peters DIPA
desc: Absolutely amazing DIPA. Really well balanced. Hard to pick out the hop type as it seems like there’s a lot mixed in there

name: Fabrik Wedding pale ale
desc: A bit hoppy, a bit tangy. Rather nice all round

name: Fabrik Pale ale
desc: A little bitter and has a strange smell and after taste but overall pretty good

name: Lübzer pils
desc: A little bitter and malty but lacking any real flavour. Not something you want more of

name: Berliner Marcus bräu red
desc: A little tangy, seems like a mix between a pilsner and a gose. Not something I would rave about, but decent

name: Berliner pilsner
desc: A little harsh to start but not too bad

name: Flensburger
desc: Pretty easy to get down. Decent session beer

name: Perlenbacher pils
desc: Cheap and malty. You can't really complain at 29¢ a can

name: Hafferöder premium pils
desc: Not exactly premium but not awful

name: Cannabis beer
desc: Really weird flavour, kind of like a sour gummy worm mixed with beer

name: Clock American red IPA
desc: Such a great hop aroma. Much milder on the palette but well balanced. Wouldn't be upset with a few of these

name: Sibeeria Baltic porter
desc: Damn this is good. So rich with a slight nuttiness. A little smokey too

name: Koala 12
desc: Really mild lager, just a little malty

name: Kozel dark unfiltered
desc: Mild in flavour and quite easy drinking. A little sweet but not malty. Not what you would expect from a dark beer

name: Excelent
desc: Not so excellent. Fairly dry and average

name: Radegast 12
desc: Your basic lager

name: Gösser märzen
desc: Another fairly plain lager. Goes down easy though

name: Ottakringer
desc: Very light lager

name: Ottakringer gold fassl
desc: Sweet and a little malty

name: Stiegl Columbus
desc: Surprising hoppy for an Austrian beer. High quality beer

name: Schwechater bier
desc: Another plain Austrian lager. A little sweet and otherwise flavourless

name: Loser bier
desc: More malty than I expected. It's ok but nothing to write home about

name: Hallstatt Das bier
desc: Really smooth but mostly flavourless

name: Eggenberg märzen
desc: A little malty and not too bitter. Sessionable

name: Hallstättersee bier
desc: Very plain beer

name: Zipfer
desc: A very thin lager

name: Edelweiss Dunkel
desc: Absolutely awesome compared to the lagers I've been having. Full of wheat and yeast but with a smooth mouthfeel

name: Egger Märzenbier
desc: Just a regular lager

name: Stiegl Weiss
desc: A great smooth weissbier with a mild yeastiness

name: Franziskaner weissbier
desc: The first time I had this it was mixed with orange and lemonade, it was still good but not what I wanted. The second time it was plain which I prefer. Decent all round weissbier

name: Hofbräu kaltenhausen
desc: Mild and well rounded lager

name: Konig Ludwig dunkel
desc: Has a strange metallic taste to it. There is a slight stoutiness but it's hard to pick

name: Augustiner märzen
desc: Surprisingly good. A little sweet but it's subtle and the beer is so well rounded that it's done before you know it

name: Castello
desc: Really good summer beer. Light and easy drinking

name: Bradipa
desc: Misses out on any big hop flavours but isn't too bitter. A fairly relaxed IPA

name: Grimbergen Blanche
desc: Easy drinking and mild yet yeasty Belgian ale

name: Grimbergen double
desc: Can really taste the candi sugar. Nicely sweet with no bitterness. Surprisingly easy to drink

name: Martens gold
desc: Mild and refreshing

name: Affen könig imperial IPA
desc: Very floral aroma and rather bitter taste. Could be a little better balanced and have some more hop flavours

name: Birra motetti grand cru
desc: Very Belgian tasting. Probably a little too harsh without having any great flavours

name: Bierschmiede zunder
desc: Really smokey flavour and even more smell. Pretty easy drinking but no other strong flavours

name: Rieder bock
desc: A little yeasty and easy drinking

name: Ichnusa
desc: Pretty smooth lager. Something just seems wrong with it

name: Baladin birra nazionale
desc: Yeasty and refreshing. The flavour tends to linger a little but there's something to this that really elevates it. Nice amount of fizz

name: Era ottanta tre
desc: Strangely good. Just that little bit of maltiness which balances out well. The kind of drink you could smash down without realising the strength

name: Fahnen bräu
desc: Basic easy drinking beer

name: Proper job
desc: Such a great smell. Taste is pretty amazing as well. Basically your perfect fruity pale ale. Delicious to the last drop

name: Goslar 1826
desc: That amazing salty refreshingness. No lingering harshness but with a slight saltiness left on your lips

name: Lambrate hazelnut porter
desc: Hazelnut is an amazing flavour that works without sweetness. Gives you exactly what you so for

name: Extraomes quadruple
desc: A really bad example of a quad. The sourness becomes slightly offensive and makes it hard to get through

name: Dolomiti pils
desc: Mild maltiness. Pretty refreshing and easy to drink

name: Birra nova margose
desc: Interesting balance. More salty than sour. Not as refreshing as I hoped

name: Bevog IPA
desc: Smells slightly spicy and earthy. Too bitter considering the lack of hop flavours

name: Gold stern
desc: Pretty plain lager

name: Brewdog hard core
desc: Dank smell. Surprisingly low on bitterness with a bit of maltiness

name: Oettinger weissbier
desc: A very mild weissbier that works well. Much better than the plain one

name: Lucifer
desc: Little bit of a metallic taste and a cheap harshness

name: Nastro azzurro
desc: Golden color with a crisp refreshing taste and nice level of fizz. Great on a hot Italian day. No good once warm

name: Williamsbrau pils
desc: Very mild, almost water beer. Good for a cheap easy drinking beer

name: Ceres Top Pilsner
desc: Pretty plain lager

name: Birra Dana
desc: Cheap boring lager
